{
  "id": "lesson_07_order_limit",
  "title": "Sorting and Limiting Results (ORDER BY & LIMIT)",
  "lesson_type": "interactive_sql",
  "objective": "Sort results with ORDER BY and limit rows with LIMIT.",
  "prerequisites": [
    "lesson_06_null"
  ],
  "estimated_minutes": 12,
  "content_markdown": "## Core Concept\n\nSorting helps analysis by organizing results.\n\nExample:\n\n```sql\nSELECT *\nFROM filtering.orders\nORDER BY amount DESC;\n```\n\nLimiting results:\n\n```sql\nSELECT *\nFROM filtering.orders\nLIMIT 10;\n```\n\n---\n\n## End of Module 2\n\nIn the next module you will learn:\n\n* Aggregations (`SUM`, `COUNT`, `AVG`)\n* `GROUP BY`\n* Real analytical SQL queries used by analysts every day.",
  "dataset_context": {
    "business_model": "core_sql",
    "tables_used": [
      "filtering.orders",
      "filtering.customers"
    ],
    "scenario": "Sort and limit query results."
  },
